org.orgName: United States District Court For The Western District of Washington Northern Division

div1.p: In the District Court of the United States for the Western District of Washington. Northern Division.
In the Matter of the Application of Chas. Jackson, for a Writ of Habeas Corpus.
div1.ab: Filed in the United States District Court Western District of Washington Northern Division

F. M. Harshberger, Clerk
By S. E. Leitch, Deputy
div1.p: In the Matter of the Application of CHAS. JACKSON for a Writ of Habeas Corpus.

Counsel for the above named applicant, Charles Jackson, and counsel fot the Government having stipulated in writing that the return on that certain order to show cause heretofore entered herein, may be continued from the 18th day of November, 1918, to the 25th day of November, 1918, at 2;00 o'clock P.M.
It is by the Court hereby considered and ordered that the return on said chow cause order be and the same hereby is continued to said 25th day of November, 1918, at 2;00 o'clock P.M.
Done in open Court this 19 day of November, 1918.

closer.signed:
Jeremiah Neterer
United States District Judge.
